Cerebration of Kim Jong Il's election as WPK General Secretary 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- A preparatory committee for celebrating the second anniversary of the election of the great leader Kim Jong Il as General Secretary of the Worker's Party of Korea and the 54th founding anniversary of the WPK was inaugurated in Romania.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Ion Cimpoiu, vice-chairman of the Socialist Party of Romania, was elected chairman of the preparatory committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   An inaugural meeting was held on September 25. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The chairman of the socialist party of Romania said at the inaugural meeting that the election of Kim Jong Il as General Secretary of the WPK is a solid guarantee for the final victory of the Juche revolutionary cause pioneered by President Kim Il Sung.

Reception on Independence Day of Nigeria
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- F. A. Oputu, charge d'affaires ad interim of the Nigerian embassy  in Pyongyang, gave a reception on Friday on the occasion of the 39th anniversary of the independence of Nigeria. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Invited there were Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly, Pyon Yong Rip, Minister of Education, officials concerned and foreign diplomatic envoys here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Speeches were made there.

Korean socialism will win
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- Madhav Kumar Nepal, general secretary of the central committee of the Nepal Communist Party (United Marxism-Leninism), who visited the DPRK emphasized that Korean socialism led by Kim Jong Il will win one victory after another. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Kim Jong Il is wisely leading the work of all domains, shouldering the heavy burdens of the Korean revolution and the members of the Worker's Party, working people and soldiers of Korea are all out to build a powerful nation under his leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The experience of Korea shows that although the  aftereffects of disasters  are very serious, the people, united firm around the great leader, are able to overcome all the difficulties and realize their cause. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Korea has a powerful force of the  single-hearted unity of the leader, party and people,  powerful military power and the solid foundation of the self-supporting national economy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   We will further develop relations with the WPK defending the banner of socialism firmly.

Withdrawal of U.S. troops from S. Korea demanded
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- The Kim Il Sung-Kim Jong Il Juche idea study groups in Vienna of Austria urged the withdrawal of the U.S. troops from South Korea and the repeal of the "National Security Law" of the South Korean authorities in a statement issued on September 24 on the  lapse of 54 years after the U.S. troops' occupation of South Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The peaceful reunification of Korea can not be realized nor can the peace of the Korean peninsula be guaranteed unless the U.S. withdraws its troops from South Korea and the South Korean authorities repeal the "National Security Law". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The Guyana Committee for Supporting Korea's  Reunification demanded the withdrawal of the U.S. troops from South Korea in a letter to the UN secretary general on Sept. 22. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   There is no reason for justifying the presence of the U.S. troops in South Korea today when the Cold War has come to an end and  their presence is a major stumbling block to the peaceful reunification of the Korean peninsula, the letter said.

S. Koreans tour different places
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- Basketball teams and working officials group of the South Korean Hyundai Business Group yesterday visited the king Tangun's mausoleum and the Pyongyang metro. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Some members of them looked round the monument to the reconstructed mausoleum of king Tangun and the monument of king Tangun's mausoleum, being briefed on the wonderful reconstruction of Tangun's mausoleum  in Kangdong county, Pyongyang as one of the nation's father. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
They carefully saw the grave-chamber where the preciousrelic proving the long history and homogeneity of the nation are preserved. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The other members looked round the Pyongyang metro.

U.S. petty trick rejected
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- Some press media of the west have described the U.S. announcement on the lifting of economic sanctions against the DPRK as "favour" to the latter. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Commenting on this fact, Minju Joson today says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The United States recently announced a plan to lift some provisions of economic sanctions against the DPRK. Though belatedly, it is fortunate for peace and stability in the Korean peninsula and the rest of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   However, the U.S. is misleading public opinion, describing as "present" the announced lifting of sanctions that should have been carried out under the DPRK-U.S. agreed framework. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In this way it seeks to secure more significant concessions from us in solving the issue of the DPRK-U.S. relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   If the U.S. is truly interested in the solution it should carry into practice the announcement on lifting of sanctions and lift the sanctions totally, not partially. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   When the U.S. shows good faith we also will approach it with good faith.

Vigorous scientific and technological activities called for
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- An enlarged meeting of the 25th plenum of the central committee of the Korean General Federation of Science and Technology was held here Friday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The meeting discussed the issues of heightening the roles of the organizations of the federation at all levels in their work to carry through the highly important tasks set forth by General Secretary Kim Jong Il during his on-site guidance to different domains of the national economy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The meeting laid stress on the need to vigorously conduct the scientific and technological activities and mass technological innovation drive for speeding  up the second grand Chollima march.

DPRK wins in women's 5,000m sprint
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- Jong Yong Ok of the DPRK raced home first in the women's 5,000m sprint of the 8th Asian Junior Track and field championships held in Singapore on September 30. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Her clocking was 16 minutes 55.28 seconds. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Another girl of the DPRK Ri Myong Sil finished second in the same event.

Senior party and state officials have photo taken
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- Senior party and state officials yesterday had a photo taken with the participants in the meeting of exemplary officials of primary organizations of the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League at the plaza of the Kumsusan Memorial Palace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Present were Kim Yong Nam, President of the presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly, Choe Thae Bok and Kim jung rin, secretaries of the Central Committee of the WPK, and the participants in the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The senior party and state officials highly praised the exemplary officials of primary organizations and all the participants for playing the nuclear role in the work of the youth league and for their great contribution to the development of the youth movement.

DPRK FM meets foreign ministers
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- Foreign Minister of the DPRK Peak Nam Sun respectively met the foreign ministers of Australia and Congo in New York on Sept. 27. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Foreign Minister of Congo said that the DPRK and Congo have maintained friendly relations from long ago and they would invariably support the Korean people's struggle for the independent and peaceful reunification of the country.

Polish charge d'affaires ad interim visits home of marathon queen 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- Polish charge d'affaires ad interim in Korea Mieczyslaw Dedo and his wife yesterday visited the home of the world "marathon queen" Jong Song Ok.   Jong Song Ok and her family greeted them gladly and had a talk with them in a friendly atmosphere. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The charge d'affaires said that the DPRK led by the great leader achieved the world-startling success in the sports and the victory showed again the Korean people are vigorously advancing, believing in their strength. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He said it is thanks to the guidance of the great leader that Jong Song Ok could be the world "marathon queen."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He looked round the house Jong Song Ok  received as a gift and gave her souvenirs.

KCNA  on provocative remarks
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- Hong Sun Yong, South Korean "Minister of Foreign Affairs and Trade," reportedly said on Wednesday that "the basic stand of the 'government'  is that South Korea  must have the capacity to develop missiles with the range of over 500 kilometers that can strike the whole area of the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
    His remarks mean that the source of dampening the prospect of affirmative developments made after the recent U.S.-DPRK talks for ensuring detente and peace on the Korean peninsula is growing like a poisonous mushroom in South Korea which is under the U.S. nuclear and missile umbrella. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   His announcement glaringly exposes the true aim of the hypocritical north policy of the present "government", which is loud-mouthed about improvement of the inter-Korean relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Particularly, it is all the more serious that the South Korean authorities under the U.S. political,  military and economic domination officially made provocative utterances pouring cold water over the DPRK-U.S. agreement at a crucial moment when good faith must be shown through the implementation of the agreement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   What is hard to understand is their announcement that they can  independently adopt a dangerous policy of missile development without their master's approval because they have no  political sovereignty and prerogative of the supreme command. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   This convinces us again of the highhandedness and arbitrariness of the U.S. which is applying the double-standard in the "missile issue."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   If the U.S. sincerely wants to implement the DPRK-U.S. agreement, it should make clear its stand as to the official statement of the South Korean "Minister of Foreign Affairs and Trade."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   And the South Korean authorities are well advised to clearly see the situation and refrain from reckless words.

"Grand" prize and diploma awarded to Kimjongilia
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- The China Kunming World Floriculture Fair '99 awarded the "grand" prize, its highest prize, and a diploma to the immortal Kimjongilia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The fair opened in Kunming city, Yunnan Province of China on May 1 and will last until the end of October. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Exhibited there were over 2,400 species of flowering trees and other plants from 69 countries and 26 international organizations of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The DPRK displayed over 200 pots of Kimjongilia and 30 odd species of ornamental plants. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   President Jiang Zemin of the People's Republic of China, the King and Queen of Cambodia, the  President of Zimbabwe and many other party, state and government heads of different countries attended its opening ceremony. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Leading officials and people of china, foreign tourists and overseas. Koreans, more than 1.1 million all told, visited the Korean wing to see Kimjongilia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   This flower had received a gold medal and a special prize at the 12th international flower show in May 1991.

Art performance on birth anniversary of Mansudae Art Troupe 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- An art performance "For three decades under guidance of the Marshal" was given yesterday at the East Pyongyang Grand Theatre to mark the 30th birth anniversary of the Mansudae Art Troupe. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The performance was seen by senior party and state officials including Kim Yong Nam and Hong Song Nam and working people in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Put on the stage were colourful numbers including poem and chorus "Korea, I will glorify thee", women's instrumental concert "Song of Loyalty", dance "Azalea of Fatherland" and  mixed duet  and chorus "We will go along the road of loyalty". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Seeing the performance the audience looked back with deep emotion upon  the immortal course  in which the respected Marshal Kim Jong Il brought about a revolution  in literature and art and ushered in the best time of the art of Juche with his outstanding and tested leadership true to the high intention of the President Kim Il Sung.

Complete abolition of "SL" in S. Korea urged
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- The joint meeting of political parties and organizations in the DPRK was held on September 30. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The participants in the meeting stressed the need for all the fellow countrymen to unite with each other to launch a powerful joint struggle for  total and complete abrogation of the "security law"  of South Korea and accelerate the cause of national reunification through nationwide struggle, and adopted an appeal to political parties and organizations in South Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   This is a very just and timely step, Rodong Sinmun stresses in a commentary today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The "security law" of South Korea is an evil law of confrontation and division opposed to national unity and reunification, and a means for fascist suppression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   As  long as this "law,"  which defines the DPRK as an "anti-state organization" and the fellow countrymen as "enemies," remains untouched in South Korea, neither dialogue and contact nor reconciliation and unity can be realized between the north and south. It is illogical for one side to call for "dialogue" and "cooperation" with the other side, its partner,  while denying its existence itself. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The past history of the north-south dialogue gives a serious lesson that  with the "security law "  left alone, it is impossible to have reunification-oriented and fruitful dialogue and contact and promote national reconciliation and unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The South Korean authorities are now talking about the "revision" of this evil law. That means rewriting its some provisions. It is a mockery and challenge to public opinion at home and abroad  calling for complete abrogation of it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The anti-reunification and anti-national "security law" should be completely and totally abolished, as demanded by the times and the nation. It is meaningless to rewrite a few provisions or terminology's of the "law,"  which incriminates the people's movement for independence, democracy and reunification, leaving its main framework untouched.  Poisonous herb should be rooted out.

Truth of mass killings by U.S. soldiers uncovered 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- The truth behind mass killings of innocent civilians by the U.S. aggression troops in Yongdong county, North Chungchong Province, during  the Korean War of aggression (1950-1953)  was reported by the AP on Sept. 29, which causes a great sensation, according to reports. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   From July 25 to 28, 1950, they killed over 400 innocent people in Yongdong county. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   At that time, they called out bombers to make air raids against the innocent people and  machine-gunned the survivors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The AP made public a  procured order of the command of the 25th division of the U.S. Army related to the massacre and reported testimonies of ex-GIs who were on the spot. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The massacre has already been disclosed by the South Korean press including the magazine mal. Its truth has been confirmed to be an irrefutable fact as it was repeatedly uncovered by documents including the order of a unit of the U.S. forces which was obtained by the AP.

Balderdash of S. Korean ruler refuted 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- The present chief executive of South Korea defamed the DPRK again at a "ceremony for 'day of ROK army'" on Friday, according to a radio report from Seoul. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He said that as the north is an "incomprehensible opponent," the south should "maintain tighter security posture."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Worse still, he argued that it is a "basic guarantee for security" to "induce" the north to make "changes." Defending the scheme to dispatch troops to East Timor, he said it is "to repay the benefit given by the united nations at the time of the June 25 Korean War."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Such utterances little different from nonsense of a sleep-walker, could be done only by an anti-reunification element. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   This revealed only the South Korean ruler's intention to provoke a war against the north and break the desire for reunification of the 70 million fellow countrymen.

Munsu Health Complex 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- The Munsu Health Complex which stands in east Pyongyang and has a total area of some 10,000 square metres is a modernly-equipped health center. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It comprises bathrooms of various shapes, barber shops, beauty parlors, an outdoor wading pool and soft-drink stands. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It is visited by 3,000 people on average a day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It is quite serviceable enough for the visitors. Special service is done to children and elderly people.

Anti-reunification repression under fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 2 (KCNA) -- Kim Ryong song, vice-chairman of the National Reconciliation Council, made public a statement today denouncing the South Korean authorities for having detained the delegates of the south side, who attended the "grand national symposium for independence and great unity" in Beijing in early August with the attendance of reunification movement organizations from the north and the south of Korea and abroad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The statement said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The South Korean authorities on Sept. 14 imprisoned Han Tong Gun, director of the southern Kyonggi provincial federation under the "National Alliance for Democracy and Reunification," and two other delegates on the charges of meeting and communication under the "National Security Law."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The arrest has been made for the mere reason that the delegates met with northerners in Beijing to hold the grand national symposium and discuss such issues as withdrawal of the U.S. forces and confederacy formula for reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   As for the symposium, it was held according to an official decision of north, south and overseas. Koreans reflecting the long-cherished desire of the nation and under the formal agreement of the three parties on problems related to it such as theme and contents, date and venue.    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Therefore, they are qualified delegates and pro-reunification champions of South Korea who participated in the symposium to carry out the decision of their organizations and contribute to the cause for reunification as members of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Nevertheless, the South Korean fascist clique arrested them after detaining the delegates of the south side to the August 15 grand pan-national pro-reunification festival. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   I, on behalf of the national reconciliation council, scathingly denounce such fascist repression as anti-national crime.    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Strongly demanding immediate release of all the pro-reunification patriots of South Korea arrested on unreasonable charges, the statement ardently called upon all the organizations of reunification movement in South Korea to actively turn out in the struggle for the total repeal of the "NSL" and freedom of activities of the pro-reunification and patriotic organizations.
